<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana" COLOR="#756155">Originally posted by exileds on 03-15-2000 02:34 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Ahh the age old argument of race choice for druids. Here is my 2 cents. I play one of those rare human druids out there.Why you ask?? Because I'm RARE!!! I ge so tired of seeing the same woodelf or halfling over and over again. I agree that humans blow for many classes, and that the halfling and woodelf stats are better. But only by 5 points in wisdom which is our prime attribute. My starting wisdom was 110, halfling and woodelf are 115 maxed. Agility and Dexterity are also better in the overplayed races,but the difference is so minor that you'll never notice. For the most part attributes dont make a big difference until they are 100 plus. Night vision? easily remedied by items/spells. And a properly built human druid will have no trouble attaining higher lvls. So my advice to our friends who aspire to the call of nature? Enjoy the game, play the race/class that you want to. I personally enjoy the fact that I am so rare amongst the conformist masses. 
                        Cyyric Wulvenblood
                          Human Treehugger
                             Rallos Zek

                         </TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
